#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:29
msgid "debugfs entries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:31
msgid ""
"The S/390 debug feature (s390dbf) generates views to hold various debug "
"results in sysfs directories of the form:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:34
msgid "/sys/kernel/debug/s390dbf/pci_*/"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:36
msgid "For example:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:38
msgid "/sys/kernel/debug/s390dbf/pci_msg/sprintf"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:40
msgid ""
"holds messages from the processing of PCI events, like machine check "
"handling and setting of global functionality, like UID checking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:43
msgid ""
"Change the level of logging to be more or less verbose by piping a number "
"between 0 and 6 to  /sys/kernel/debug/s390dbf/pci_*/level. For details, see "
"the documentation on the S/390 debug feature at Documentation/arch/s390/"
"s390dbf.rst."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:49
msgid "Sysfs entries"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:51
msgid ""
"Entries specific to zPCI functions and entries that hold zPCI information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:53
msgid "/sys/bus/pci/slots/XXXXXXXX:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:55
msgid ""
"The slot entries are set up using the function identifier (FID) of the PCI "
"function as slot name. The format depicted as XXXXXXXX above is 8 "
"hexadecimal digits with 0 padding and lower case hexadecimal digits."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:59
msgid "/sys/bus/pci/slots/XXXXXXXX/power"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:61
msgid ""
"In addition to using the FID as the name of the slot, the slot directory "
"also contains the following s390-specific slot attributes."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:64
msgid ""
"uid: The User-defined identifier (UID) of the function which may be "
"configured by this slot. See also the corresponding attribute of the device."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:68
msgid ""
"A physical function that currently supports a virtual function cannot be "
"powered off until all virtual functions are removed with: echo 0 > /sys/bus/"
"pci/devices/DDDD:BB:dd.f/sriov_numvf"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:72
msgid "/sys/bus/pci/devices/DDDD:BB:dd.f/:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:74
msgid ""
"function_id: The zPCI function identifier (FID) is a 32-bit hexadecimal "
"value that uniquely identifies the PCI function. Unless the hypervisor "
"provides a virtual FID e.g. on KVM this identifier is unique across the "
"machine even between different partitions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:80
msgid ""
"function_handle: This 32-bit hexadecimal value is a low-level identifier "
"used for a PCI function. Note that the function handle may be changed and "
"become invalid on PCI events and when enabling/disabling the PCI function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:85
msgid ""
"pchid: This 16-bit hexadecimal value encodes a model-dependent location for "
"the PCI function."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:89
msgid ""
"pfgid: PCI function group ID; functions that share identical functionality "
"use a common identifier. A PCI group defines interrupts, IOMMU, IOTLB, and "
"DMA specifics."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:94
msgid ""
"vfn: The virtual function number, from 1 to N for virtual functions, 0 for "
"physical functions."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:98
msgid ""
"pft: The PCI function type is an s390-specific type attribute. It indicates "
"a more general, usage oriented, type than PCI Specification class/vendor/"
"device identifiers. That is PCI functions with the same pft value may be "
"backed by different hardware implementations. At the same time apart from "
"unclassified functions (pft is 0x00) the same pft value generally implies a "
"similar usage model. At the same time the same PCI hardware device may "
"appear with different pft values when in a different usage model. For "
"example NETD and NETH VFs may be implemented by the same PCI hardware device "
"but in NETD the parent Physical Function is user managed while with NETH it "
"is platform managed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:110
msgid "Currently the following PFT values are defined:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:112
msgid "0x00 (UNC): Unclassified"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:113
msgid "0x02 (ROCE): RoCE Express"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:114
msgid "0x05 (ISM): Internal Shared Memory"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:115
msgid "0x0a (ROC2): RoCE Express 2"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:116
msgid "0x0b (NVMe): NVMe"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:117
msgid "0x0c (NETH): Network Express hybrid"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:118
msgid "0x0d (CNW): Cloud Network Adapter"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:119
msgid "0x0f (NETD): Network Express direct"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:121
msgid ""
"port: The port is a decimal value corresponding to the physical port the "
"function is attached to. Virtual Functions (VFs) share the port with their "
"parent Physical Function (PF). A value of 0 indicates that the port "
"attribute is not applicable for that PCI function type."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:127
msgid ""
"uid: The user-defined identifier (UID) for a PCI function is a 32-bit "
"hexadecimal value. It is defined on a per instance basis as part of the "
"partition, KVM guest, or z/VM guest configuration. If UID Checking is "
"enabled the platform ensures that the UID is unique within that instance and "
"no two PCI functions with the same UID will be visible to the instance."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:134
msgid ""
"Independent of this guarantee and unlike the function ID (FID) the UID may "
"be the same in different partitions within the same machine. This allows to "
"create PCI configurations in multiple partitions to be identical in the UID-"
"namespace."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:139
msgid ""
"uid_is_unique: A 0 or 1 flag indicating whether the user-defined identifier "
"(UID) is guaranteed to be and remain unique within this Linux instance. This "
"platform feature is called UID Checking."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:144
msgid ""
"pfip/segmentX: The segments determine the isolation of a function. They "
"correspond to the physical path to the function. The more the segments are "
"different, the more the functions are isolated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:149
msgid ""
"fidparm: Contains an 8-bit-per-PCI function parameter field in hexadecimal "
"provided by the platform. The meaning of this field is PCI function type "
"specific. For NETH VFs a value of 0x01 indicates that the function supports "
"promiscuous mode."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:155
msgid "/sys/firmware/clp/uid_checking:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:157
msgid ""
"In addition to the per-device uid_is_unique attribute this presents a global "
"indication of whether UID Checking is enabled. This allows users to check "
"for UID Checking even when no PCI functions are configured."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:162
msgid "Enumeration and hotplug"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:164
msgid ""
"The PCI address consists of four parts: domain, bus, device and function, "
"and is of this form: DDDD:BB:dd.f."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:167
msgid ""
"For a PCI function for which the platform does not expose the RID, the "
"pci=norid kernel parameter is used, or a so-called isolated Virtual Function "
"which does have RID information but is used without its parent Physical "
"Function being part of the same PCI configuration:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:172
msgid "There is only one function per domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:174
msgid ""
"The domain is set from the zPCI function's UID if UID Checking is on; "
"otherwise the domain ID is generated dynamically and is not stable across "
"reboots or hot plug."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:178
msgid ""
"For a PCI function for which the platform exposes the RID and which is not "
"an Isolated Virtual Function:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:181
msgid "There is still only one bus per domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:183
msgid "There can be up to 256 PCI functions per bus."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:185
msgid ""
"The domain part of the address of all functions within the same topology is "
"that of the configured PCI function with the lowest devfn within that "
"topology."
msgstr ""

#: ../../../arch/s390/pci.rst:189
msgid ""
"Virtual Functions generated by an SR-IOV capable Physical Function only "
"become visible once SR-IOV is enabled."
msgstr ""
